To fix the SQL Injection vulnerability in the provided Java code, we need to use PreparedStatements instead of directly concatenating user input into the SQL query. PreparedStatements provide a way to create parameterized queries, which separate SQL code from user input, preventing malicious input from altering the structure of the query.

Here is the updated code snippet with proper security measures using PreparedStatement:

